x4freetext: 10 g of Nd2-O3 enriched to 97.4% in Nd-146.
Cuboidal shape 43x34x3 mm**3 ,30 degrees with the
neutron beam.
40 cm3 coaxial Ge(Li) detector with 3 keV FWHM
for 1332 keV gamma rays, placed 40 cm from target.
No further information
Fast-neutron beam extracted from reactor was filtered
from thermal neutrons and gamma rays by 0.5 mm of Cd,
1 cm of B4-C and 5 cm of depleted uranium. A system
of collimators was used to obtain a beam diameter of
about 4 cm on the target.
At 1.5 MeV neutron spectrum falls off according to the
exp(-0.72E(n))-law approximately.(Nucl.Inst.and Meth.
